In cases where the LDAP user directory is read/write, the logs will report the password complexity errors but the user sees a generic "Sorry, but your password could not be changed". 

It would be helpful if the messages from the logs were passed to the Confluence UI.

Examples from the logs are:

\{code}LDAP: error code 19 - 0000052D: Constraint violation - check_password_restrictions: the password does not meet the complexity criteria!]\{code}

\{code}[LDAP: error code 19 - 0000052D: Constraint violation - check_password_restrictions: the password is too short. It should be equal or longer than 8 characters!\{code}

If these errors were seen by the users they would be able to comply with the restrictions, as it is, they do not know why the password cannot be changed.

