When displaying several JIRA pie charts on a single Confluence page, it looks like the "first" status returned is color blue, the next is orange, the next is green, etc.  While you might think that is "consistent", it's really not when one pie chart shows all issues are CLOSED (in blue), and the next shows all issues are OPEN (also in blue).

Each status should have a consistent color (maybe matched to the standard JIRA colors of To Do = Blue, In Progress = Yellow, Closed/Done = Green).  Or, allow the colors to be customized inside the JIRA chart macro.

Please see the attached for a great example of how 2 different charts "look the same" but in fact should be telling very different stories.

